Count 1 - Deliver Imitation Substance - No contest plea.  Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, theft.  Motion granted.   Sentence is withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Obtain high school diploma within first 6 months;
2) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
3) Reimburse metro drug for $255.00 buy money;
4) AODA assessment and follow through;
5) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
6) Maintain absolute sobriety;
7) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
8) Comply with all counseling;
9) Ninety (90) days jail, imposed and stayed, to be imposed upon the agent's discretion;
10) Pay costs of action;
11) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
12) Submit DNA sample.   
Probation review hearing set for 06-09-15 at 3:30 p.m.   
